The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, Dec. 18 (PTI): The Centre today tabled in the Lok Sabha the Ranganath Mishra panel report that has recommended 10 per cent quota for Muslims and other minorities in government jobs and Scheduled Caste status for Dalits of all religions.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): The government has decided to implement a visa-on-arrival scheme for citizens of five countries  Singapore, Japan, New Zealand, Luxembourg and Finland. The scheme will apply for a year as an experiment.                   
	 Chennai: Madras High Court has declined to overturn the acquittal of Abdul Nasser Madhani, leader of Keralas PDP, in the Coimbatore serial blasts in 1998. But his wife Sufiya was remanded in judicial custody after being denied bail in a bus-burning case.                  
	New Delhi: The army has pulled out nearly 30,000 troops from Jammu and Kashmir over the past year because for the first time law and order is improving, said defence minister A.K. Antony.                                                                                                                                               
